OL,5, Labelling foods as ultra-processed     
OL,6, might not be so helpful for consumers  
OL,7, who want to know how healthy a product 
OL,8, is, UK experts say.                    
OL,10,FCurrently, packs must show whether a   
OL,11,Ffood item is high in fat, salt and     
OL,12,Fsugar but not how processed it is.     
OL,14,FScientists who analysed different      
OL,15,Fproducts say it is too simplistic to   
OL,16,Fbrand all ultra-processed foods (UPFs) 
OL,17,Fas very bad.                           
OL,19,FTechnically, sliced bread is           
OL,20,Fultra-processed, for example.          
